Task: Refine the Corefinity Control Panel with strict functional logic and premium UI interactions as per the specification document.
​1. The "Sequential Dropdown" Logic (Environments > Deployments):  
​Implement a "New Repository" form with four dropdowns: Pipeline, Provider, Repository, and Branch.
​Strict Rule: Each dropdown must be disabled until the one immediately before it has a value selected.
​Validation: If "Provider" is selected but no account is linked, display a high-visibility warning: "⚠️ No account connected. Please link a provider in Profile > API Tokens."  
​The "Confirm & Save" button must remain disabled until all 4 fields are valid.
​2. The "Dual-Communication" System (Tickets View):  
​In the Ticket Detail view, implement a clearer distinction between Internal and External replies.
​Internal Comment (Staff Only): When this tab/toggle is active, the message area background must change to a subtle Yellow (#FFFBEB) and the primary button should say "Post Internal Note."
​Send Reply (Customer Visible): When active, use the standard white background and brand-orange "Send Reply" button.
​Metadata Sidebar: Ensure the ticket detail page always shows the Company, Agency, and Website as OrangeLink components in the right-hand sidebar.  
​3. Real-Time Task Simulation (Deployment Tasks):  
​In the Deployment Tasks tab, the most recent task must be at the top.
​Give the top task a "Running" status with a pulsing green indicator. All previous tasks should show "Succeeded" with a "Rollback" action button.  
​4. Global Navigation "Orange Rule":  
​Audit the entire site: Ensure every mention of a Company, Website, or Environment is rendered using the OrangeLink component.
​Ensure the top breadcrumb is dynamic (e.g., All Clients > Example Agency > Production Env).
​5. UI Polish:
​Add a "Copy to Clipboard" icon next to IP addresses in the Firewall tab and API Tokens in the Profile tab.
​Use a "skeleton loader" or a clean transition when switching between the many horizontal tabs in the Environments view. 
